\int_0^1 \frac{u^{2k}}{1+u} du = \int_0^1 \frac{u^{2k}-1}{1+u} du + \int_0^1 \frac{1}{1+u} du
\int_0^1 \frac{u^{2k}-1}{1+u} du = - \int_0^1 \left(\sum_{m=0}^{2k-1} (-u)^m du \right) = \sum_{m=0}^{2k-1} (-1)^{m+1} \int_0^1 u^m du = \sum_{m=0}^{2k-1} \frac{(-1)^{m+1}}{m+1}
\int_0^1 \frac{1}{1+u} du = \log(2)
I_{n} = n \log(2) + n \times \sum_{m=1}^{n-1} \frac{(-1)^m}{m}
\int_0^1 \frac{u^{2k-1}}{1+u} du = \int_0^1 \frac{u^{2k-1}+1}{1+u} du - \int_0^1 \frac{1}{1+u} du
\int_0^1 \frac{u^{2k-1}+1}{1+u} du = \int_0^1 \left(\sum_{m=0}^{2k-2} (-u)^m du \right) = \sum_{m=0}^{2k-2} (-1)^{m} \int_0^1 u^m du = \sum_{m=0}^{2k-2} \frac{(-1)^{m}}{m+1}
\int_0^1 \frac{1}{1+u} du = \log(2)
I_{n} = -n \log(2) + n \times \sum_{m=1}^{n-1} \frac{(-1)^{m-1}}{m}
C_n = n \times (-1)^n \times \sum_{m=1}^{n-1} \frac{(-1)^{m-1}}{m}
